## Follow it with database inserts

The next changesets can move distinct records from staging into the real tables.

```yaml
  - changeSet:
      id: 007-02-import-users
      author: rahul
      changes:
        - sql:
            dbms: postgresql
            sql: |
              INSERT INTO users (
                  user_id,
                  username,
                  gps_group_number,
                  source_personal_id,
                  entity,
                  first_name,
                  last_name,
                  email,
                  phone_number,
                  language,
                  status
              )
              SELECT DISTINCT
                  LOWER(TRIM(gps_group_number)),
                  LOWER(TRIM(gps_group_number)),
                  LOWER(TRIM(gps_group_number)),
                  source_personal_id,
                  entity,
                  first_name,
                  surname,
                  email,
                  phone_number,
                  language,
                  user_status
              FROM user_import_staging
              WHERE gps_group_number IS NOT NULL
                AND TRIM(gps_group_number) <> ''
              ON CONFLICT (user_id) DO UPDATE SET
                  source_personal_id = EXCLUDED.source_personal_id,
                  entity = EXCLUDED.entity,
                  first_name = EXCLUDED.first_name,
                  last_name = EXCLUDED.last_name,
                  email = EXCLUDED.email,
                  phone_number = EXCLUDED.phone_number,
                  language = EXCLUDED.language,
                  status = EXCLUDED.status;
```

