## Important deployment behavior

Once Liquibase executes a changeset, its `id`, `author`, and file path are recorded in `DATABASECHANGELOG`. Replacing the contents of the same CSV later will not cause the already-executed changeset to run again.

For a new import file, create a new changeset:

```text
008-bulk-import-users.yaml
users-bulk-import-20260725.csv
```

Do not modify the CSV attached to an already-deployed changeset unless it has never run in any shared environment.

Also, this import bypasses Java and therefore bypasses Ping provisioning. It creates database records only; Ping synchronization would need a separate post-import process.

